--- !u!114 &1642650860
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1642650858}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 43aaff53c6a392941b7c17d0dfd87d94, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  dialogueText: {fileID: 1413781446}
  dialogue:
  - dialogueName: Hunter
    dialogueText: 'Ok Watch, that''s not happening. the doors locked and blocked. '
  - dialogueName: Watch
    dialogueText: Ah not good, so the map is showing an alternate route that would
      take you through some service corridors
  - dialogueName: Hunter
    dialogueText: K
  - dialogueName: Watch
    dialogueText: 'Alright boss, I''ve worked with you for 2 months and have never
      seen you like this. Something''s clearly bothering you. I''m willing to listen
      if you''re willing to share '
  - dialogueName: Hunter
    dialogueText: "I... <b><i>*heavy sigh*</i></b>  thing is this has been worrying
      me for a while. The company says they don't feel nothin, but they\u2019re not
      out here looking at these ghosts' faces."
  - dialogueName: Watch
    dialogueText: 'But they''re corrupted in this world.So surely what you''re doing
      is a small hurt to cure their torment. Like when you break a leg and it''s
      bent out of shape, the doctor needs to snap it back, right? '
  - dialogueName: Watch
    dialogueText: 'And that snap is a short amount of pain. But only after your leg
      can begin to heal effectively '
  - dialogueName: Hunter
    dialogueText: I guess
  - dialogueName: Watch
    dialogueText: "So what you're doing for these spirits is something noble; you\u2019re
      snapping them back to the place where they can heal, as far as i'm concerned
      what you're doing is a good thing. "
  - dialogueName: Hunter
    dialogueText: 'Thanks, watch, sorry. '
  - dialogueName: Watch
    dialogueText: 'Nothing to thank me for. It hurts to see you in pain. '
  audio1: {fileID: 1048820864}
  audio2: {fileID: 0}
