--- !u!114 &1722822190
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1722822188}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 43aaff53c6a392941b7c17d0dfd87d94, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  dialogueText: {fileID: 1413781446}
  dialogue:
  - dialogueName: Watch
    dialogueText: 'Ok you should be in the service corridor, be careful there seems
      to be a few ghosts in here '
  - dialogueName: Hunter
    dialogueText: 'Aha don''t worry about the spookums, nothing I haven''t dealt
      with before. '
  - dialogueName: Watch
    dialogueText: ' At least it is good cardio I suppose'
  - dialogueName: Hunter
    dialogueText: Yeah keeps me lean, mean and......
  - dialogueName: Priest
    dialogueText: 'How many more? hmm? I know you can hear me. I may not be able
      to hear you but I can sense you. the closer you get the more of you I can feel,
      and all I feel now is your anger. '
  - dialogueName: Priest
    dialogueText: so tell me how many more tormented souls are enough to satiate
      such rage?
  - dialogueName: Hunter
    dialogueText: wonderful...
  - dialogueName: Priest
    dialogueText: Yes, I felt that! I felt your fury! what is it that makes you so
      angry? you lost pathetic man. No doubt you have no one who cares for you. Does
      my flock's love for me cause you such hatred?
  - dialogueName: Priest
    dialogueText: '<b><i>* scoffs*</i></b> again I felt your anger, did my words
      touch a nerve ? Have I determined your core, that of an angry lonely man with
      no heart? <b><i>* scoffs*</i></b> You really are a wretch '
  - dialogueName: Watch
    dialogueText: You know he's wrong boss, he's just trying to hurt you
  - dialogueName: Watch
    dialogueText: "Look you\u2019re a kind man. I'm sure tonnes of people care about
      you, I certainly do and ......"
  - dialogueName: Watch
    dialogueText: I'm sure your mom does even if your dad doesn't
  - dialogueName: Hunter
    dialogueText: My mum died when I was 15 ...
  - dialogueName: Hunter
    dialogueText: 'Eh it''s ancient history, <b><i>*heavy sigh*</i></b> At least
      she doesn''t have to sit through any more of my marathons '
  - dialogueName: Watch
    dialogueText: 'I.. I guess that''s good '
  - dialogueName: Hunter
    dialogueText: 'I joke but... I loved seeing her there. It always made me run
      a little faster ya know '
  audio1: {fileID: 1048820864}
  audio2: {fileID: 0}
